	<title>Examples of Types of Matrices</title>
	<caption>Matrix Types</caption>
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>A matrix is square shaped if it is of type <latex>(n,n)</latex>. For example, the matrices below are square shaped.</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					\left[
					\begin{array}{rr}
					6 & 9 \\
					-9 & 6
					\end{array}
					\right] \qquad
					\left[
					\begin{array}{rrr}
					4 & -4 & 1 \\
					3 & 2 & 3 \\
					1 & -3 & 6
					\end{array}
					\right] \qquad 
					\left[
					\begin{array}{rrrrr}
					3 & 0 & 2 & 4 & 3 \\
					6 & 1 & 4 & 2 & 0 \\
					1 & 5 & 7 & 6 & 9 \\
					6 & 2 & 4 & 7 & 4 \\
					3 & 3 & 3 & 0 & 3
					\end{array}
					\right] 
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>Indeed, the matrix on the left has size <latex>(2,2)</latex>. The matrix in the middle has size <latex>(3,3)</latex>. The matrix on the right has size <latex>(5,5)</latex></para>
		</statement>
	</showme>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Determine if the following matrix is square shaped.</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
				<![CDATA[
				\left[
				\begin{array}{rrrrrrr}
				6 & 5 & 3 & 12 & 19 & 403 & 121 \\
				3 & 0 & 0 & 1 & 21 & -12 & 11 \\
				1 & 1 & 2 & 2 & 4 & 4 & 8
				\end{array}
				\right]
				]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>The given matrix is not square shaped as its number of rows is <latex>3</latex>, while its number of columns is <latex>7\neq 3</latex>.</para>
		</answer>
	</showme>	
</showme.pack>